<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="507" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,258,1398]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,294,258,283]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
Diagnosis 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[266,294,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">—</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Fastigium slightly curved forward. Distance between the pronotal spines in the following way: at the bases 
<number box="[219,252,294,318]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="1.8">1.8</number>
–2.0 mm; at the apices 
<number box="[515,549,294,318]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="5.7">5.7</number>
–6.0 mm. Metazonal spine 
<number box="[856,891,294,318]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as the fastigium and with the base as wide as three-quarters of its the length. Dorsal spine of the fore tibia longer than the width of the tympanum. Branches of male cerci similar in form and without denticulations on the ventral edge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
